casebody.data:
CONRAD et al. v. ROSENTHAL. (Common Pleas of New York City and County,

General Term.

May 8, 1893.) Action by Samuel Conrad and another against Joseph Rosenthal.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

No opinion. Motion for leave to appeal to the court of appeals or for a reargument denied, with $10 costs. See 20 N. Y. Supp. 632.
